RACE.FOOTNOTES: GLENGARRY vied outside of DON JUAN BUBBA up the backstretch then shook free near the seven sixteenths pole, held firm under pressure from ORE MINE around the turn, saved ground turning for home, roused for more in upper stretch, responded willingly and drew off while ridden out. ORE MINE was well placed tracking the top pair in early stages, edged up closer and applied pressure to GLENGARRY around the turn, was no match for pulling away winner in upper stretch but sustained bid and finished clearly second best. FIRESPITTEN KITTEN raced in the back up the backstretch, hustled along four wide into upper stretch, churned on through the lane and cleared the rest.
